</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A> at: 4/8/02 5:09:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riggen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Roving Eye of Serilis</span><br>  Posts: 862<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 5:11:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11330.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: reply</span><hr size=1> Saying that Clerics were meant to be the only good healers is a lot like saying that they were meant to have nearly as much difficulty getting around as melees or that they were meant to need a group in order to play.<br>
<br>
Balancing is a two way street. Take a look over on EQ Cleric if you want to see some really entertaining ideas(Slow, nukes even better than the upgraded Judgement, DoT comparable to Winged Death, ports to temples, self only Sow, Snare) Clerics have for game balance. They want to retain a lock on healing, yet they also want a broader scope than they already have. Clerics can't have it both ways. For their balance concerns to be addressed, the concerns of the others classes must also come under scrutiny. Otherwise it isn't balancing at all. The document Relbeek mentions recognizes this and in fact specifically mentions it. <br>
<br>
Please drop the straw man arguments regarding Complete Heal. I don't know of any Druid or Shaman that has ever seriously contended that it should be castable by anyone but a Cleric. Personally I think the game as a whole would be better if Complete Heal had never been implemented.<br>
