<br>
Superior Healing should be bumped down to 44, Chloroblast 51, Nature's Touch for Druids at 56ish, and new healing spells for both classes at 60 that directly heal over 1,000 life. Perhaps 1,200 to 1,500. Torpor would stay at 60; that's a damn nice spell that needs no changing.<br>
<br>
I know when I'm in a place where mobs double for 200-300 at a minimum (weaker ToV mobs), I would prefer casting a 1,000 - 1,500 point heal  on someone, over Chloroblast/Superior Healing, which most mobs can eat through in 1-2 hits. The mana cost can be high, yes... but that wouldn't bother me at all. <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54850>Gloobonious</a></b><br>60th Ogre Shaman<br>Proud Member of <b><a href=http://eq.spknet.com>Guardians of the Relics</a></b>.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r It's a zero exp rez.</span><br>  Posts: 1701<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 5:35:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11330.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Friends/LilKegger.gif WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: reply</span><hr size=1> Generally I'm dealing with 55-58th level paladins/sks/warriors with just cleric buffs. My 51st level warrior hits about 3500 when I buff him so I was basing it off that.<br>
