<br>
What percentage of groupings- across all servers 24x7 use those hefty tanks? And of those- where is the damage accruing at such a pace that a larger heal is needed?<br>
<br>
Please- show your proof.  Without documentation it is all personal opinion.  <br>
<br>
Break down your numbers by raid vs normal experience camps.  I really have no problem with personal opinion- I just want everyone to acknowledge fact vs opinion.<br>
<br>
Your argument is that the larger heal is needed for those tanks.  But I am saying you are giving a heal that is available *all * the time for a narrow situation  That bigger heal can be used on smaller targets- enabling druids to more effectively replace clerics in normal situations.  Giving that larger heal will mean that more clerics are lfg in normal xp camps - where that cheal isnt needed.  If druids are lfg- think about it- they can go solo.  The cleric isnt able to do so as easily. <br>
<br>
Honestly, Shaiel made 60 FAST. The ability to solo mobs, travel easily, let *alone* quad is enormous.  Leo was my first char.  He still isnt 60.  Travel is a pain. Soloing?  He could- but sheesh there is no comparison to what Shaiel can do.  Now, if he dies- he can rez himself.  Yay. Shaiel doesnt die unless the lag monster gets her.  Snare, invis, gate/ port/ egress.  She is almost unkillable.  <br>
<br>
Look at the druids grove and read the things druids dare to do themselves- solo the Kael arena for armor, for example.  Solo the phase spiders in DN for a carapace.  What cleric would dare??<br>
<br>
It is a balancing act- flexibility vs specificity.  You cant remove the cleric from the group and replace with a druid and say &quot;oh well, if we die we will buy a rez.&quot;  Shouldnt happen. Other changes should happen as well- not only does the killing go slower- you should increase the damage output and add a slower.  <br>
<br>
You *cant* be everything and useful to every group in the same way.<br>
<br>
Like Rani- I play both classes.  Both are 55+.  So I have worn both hats, walked in both shoes ... (out of  metaphors here).  I dont consider Shaiel and Leo interchangeable.  When my friends and I are deciding where we want to go and what we want to do- we consider which char would be best to achieve what we want.<br>
